The '''Eino Leino Prize''' is an annual prize award to top writers in [[Finland]] since 1956, with particular emphasis on poets.<ref name="kirjasaatio">{{cite web|title=Literary prizes awarded by the Finnish Book Foundation|url=http://kirjasaatio.fi/&lang=en-gb|website=kirjasaatio.fi|accessdate=3 October 2017}}</ref><ref name="majander">{{cite news|last1=Majander|first1=Antti|title=Eino Leinon palkinto muuttunee runojen ja novellien Finlandiaksi|url=https://www.hs.fi/kulttuuri/art-2000003385534.html|accessdate=3 October 2017|publisher=Helsingin Sanomat|date=November 23, 1994}}</ref>
It is named after [[Eino Leino]], a pioneer of [[Finnish poetry]].
