{{KF Drita sections}}
'''KF Drita''' is a [[basketball]] club based in [[Gjilan]], [[Kosovo]]{{ref label|status|a|}} (''Gjilan'' is the [[Albanian language|Albanian]] name of the town).

Created in 1958, the club won the Basketball Superleague of Kosovo in 1996. KF Drita also has a women's club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://basketball.eurobasket.com/team/Kosovo/KB-Drita-Gjilan/5146 |title=KB Drita Gjilan basketball, News, Roster, Rumors, Stats, Awards, Transactions, Details - eurobasket.com |website=Basketball.eurobasket.com |date= |accessdate=2016-12-27}}</ref>

==History==
The club was formed in 1958 with the name "Drita" which means "light" in the Albanian language. The name was taken from other sports clubs in the city.

