[[File:Djibouti National Highway.png|thumb|Map of Djibouti national highway]]
'''National Highway 2''' is a major national highway of [[Djibouti]]. It connects [[Djibouti City]] to [[Loyada]] and the [[Somalia|Somali]] border, where it continues to [[Saylac]]. The highway begins at a roundabout in Djibouti City at {{coord|11|34|7|N|43|7|51|E|}} where it becomes [[National Highway 1 (Djibouti)|National Highway 1]]. It passes through the city and for much of its length passes along the coast of Djibouti on the way to Loyada.

