{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians --> | name = Nexus | image = | caption = | image_size = | background = group_or_band | alias = | origin = [[Estonia]] | genre = [[Pop music]] | years_active = 2003-2006 | label = | associated_acts = | website = | current_members = [[Janne Saar]], [[Merlyn Uusküla]], [[Helen Randmäe]] | past_members = }}
'''Nexus''' was an [[Estonia]]n pop band formed in 2003 which split up in 2006. It consisted of the singers Janne Saar, Merlyn Uusküla and Helen Randmäe. The first two albums had mostly an electronic up-tempo and general pop sound, though their last album had some rock influences. Their live band featured drummer Boriss Hrebtukov, bassist Viljar Norman and guitarist Kristjan Kaasik.
